\begin_layout Standard
The initial window displayed by OHReplay when it starts up contains all
 the information you need to know to navigate the program: To open a frame,
 use the System Menu, the Ctrl-O keystroke combination (that is a capital
 oh, the letter between N and P), or the F2 key.
 Any of these choices will open the standard Windows file open dialog, from
 where you can choose the HTML file of the frame to open.
 To navigate between frames, use Tab or Shift-Tab to move to the next or
 previous numerical frame.
 To return to the initial screen, press Esc.
\end_layout

